column1: So we're finally at Konoe's home base, huh?

Man, too bad we had to come here for Phantom
Thief biz... We coulda stuffed ourselves stupid.
Well, Sophia? Is there a Jail nearby?
I guess that settles it, then.

Now if Ichinose-san could just find that
business card...

...This is it, you guys. Do or die. We're gonna
take that asshole Konoe down and settle this
once and for all.
Whoa, look who decided to step their game up.

Think maybe his new Persona ability's goin' to
his head?
If this were a movie, you'd probably be taken out within the next 30 minutes.
Gimme a friggin' break! I'm just sayin' we should be ready, all right!?

Luckily, we won't have to worry about getting
caught by the police. Still, we'll want to be
good and ready for what's ahead.

Well, Osaka is Japan's kitchen—I can't imagine
a better place to provide us with a pre-battle
meal.
And there's plenty else here for us, too.
By the way, is Akane-chan okay?

Yeah, she was up and at 'em this morning. She's
with her grandparents right now.
I really owe you guys. Thanks.
...I dunno why, but it's weird hearin' you thank us like that, Gramps.

Ahaha. Well, it's not like he made the best first
impression.
Yeah, yeah, can't trust the police and all that...

Getting back to business, though, do you guys
have a plan to get Konoe's keyword?

Ichinose? Oh, right. The woman who designed
EMMA.

[1B]S1, Ichinose is calling. I'll put it
on speaker.

Goood morning, Phantom Thieves! How's
everyone been?
Did you have any luck getting the keyword?
Hahaha, did you forget who you're talking to?
Of course I found it! No problem whatsoever!

Now then, without further ado, Akira Konoe's
keyword is...
Zephyrman... Is that what I think it is?

It's an old live-action superhero series. Y'know,
the kind where they transform and fight evil
and stuff.
It's got somewhat of a cult following, but, for the most part, it's pretty small time. Konoe must be a big superhero buff.
So it's a superhero TV show? Why would he have something like that as his keyword?

Well, whatever his reason, we can enter the Jail
now. Thank you for your help, Ichinose-san.

Nonsense, it was easy. Besides, hearing you guys
go about your business truly brightens my day.

I guess I am pretty amazing, but it's kind of
embarrassing when someone else points it out.

Anyhow, the real fight is only just beginning,
right? Make sure you don't get yourselves killed
out there.

Alrighty, I can't wait to hear all the juicy details
when you get back. Adiós, Phantom Thieves!

If things go accordin' to plan, this'll be the last
one!

Right. Changing Konoe's heart should bring an
end to the Change of Heart epidemic.

Man, this is turnin' out to be one hell of a
summer vacation.

I'll say. We ended up traveling nearly the whole
country.
We're not done just yet. Not until we knock Konoe off his perch and make it safely back to Tokyo.
You know what they say! It ain't over till it's over!
Hey, are you sure it's okay for you to be hanging around us, Zenkichi? You're not gonna get fired or anything?
Come on, you're not gonna make me sit out for the finale, are you?

That bastard Konoe's gonna get what's coming to
him. Plus, it's time you kids cleared your names.
And let's not forget Owada... I'm bringing him in, too.

Indeed. We cannot return to our own lives until
we expose his misdeeds.
All right, whaddya say we get goin'!
Can you find us the best entry point, Sophia?
